page_description: Learn more about what you should take into consideration before fine-tuning with Azure OpenAI Service
chunk_title: What data are you going to use for fine-tuning?
chunk_content: What data are you going to use for fine-tuning?Even with a great use case, fine-tuning is only as good as the quality of the data that you're able to provide. You need to be willing to invest the time and effort to make fine-tuning work. Different models will require different data volumes but you often need to be able to provide fairly large quantities of high-quality curated data.Another important point is even with high quality data if your data isn't in the necessary format for fine-tuning you'll need to commit engineering resources in order to properly format the data.| Data  | Babbage-002 & Davinci-002 | GPT-3.5-Turbo ||---|---|---|| Volume | Thousands of Examples | Thousands of Examples || Format | Prompt/Completion | Conversational Chat |If you are ready for fine-tuning you:- Have identified a dataset for fine-tuning.- The dataset is in the appropriate format for training.- Some level of curation has been employed to ensure dataset quality.Common signs you might not be ready for fine-tuning yet:- Dataset hasn't been identified yet.- Dataset format doesn't match the model you wish to fine-tune.
